 content="""
In more detail: the names of the files you download and save should be:

* tails-i386-0.16/tails-i386-0.16.iso
* tails-i386-0.16.iso.pgp
* tails-signing.key

Those are respectively

* the iso image (the big file)
* the detached signature
* the signing key

So the shell commands in Linux (Windows should be similar) should be:

    gpg --import tails-signing.key
    gpg --verify tails-i386-0.16.iso.pgp tails-i386-0.16/tails-i386-0.16.iso


"""]]
